# 🛡️ File Integrity Monitoring (FIM) with Wazuh

## 📌 Objective
This project demonstrates the implementation and analysis of **File Integrity Monitoring (FIM)** using Wazuh.  
The goal is to detect unauthorized file changes and ensure system security through continuous monitoring.

---

## ⚙️ Environment Setup

- 🖥️ Operating System: Ubuntu (Linux)
- 🛡️ Wazuh Manager: Installed on 192.168.0.152
- 💻 Wazuh Agent: Installed on 192.168.0.181
- 🔐 Access: Root / sudo privileges
- ⚙️ Config File: `/var/ossec/etc/ossec.conf`

---

## 🔧 Configuration Steps

### Access Wazuh Server (Manager)
```bash
ssh wazuh-user@192.168.0.152

### Open Configuration File on Manager
```bash
sudo nano /var/ossec/etc/ossec.conf
